entry.title: [chrome][android][selection] Add padding to list menu divider
entry.content:
Chrome UX has requested that we add padding to the horizontal divider

in Chrome's drop-down text selection menu (similar to other menus).

The padding appears to be equal to the padding for the list menu item

in general, therefore this dimension has been abstracted and used

within `ChromeSelectionDropdownMenuDelegate` for the divider padding.



A binder for the divider has also been added to propagate the dynamic

padding.

entry.title: [Autofill] Remove AutofillDriver::RendererIsAvailable()
entry.content:
RendererIsAvailable() was introduced in [1] before Autofill used Mojo.

The checks appear not to be effective today:



RendererIsAvailable() checks whether RFHIplm::render_view_host_ is

non-nullptr. This is always the case because render_view_host_ is a

scoped_refptr which, according to its documentation,

> is kept alive as long as any RenderFrameHosts or

> RenderFrameProxyHosts are using it.



Perhaps a more useful implementation of RendererIsAvailable() would

call RFH::IsRenderFrameLive(). That seems redundant, too, because

ContentAutofillDriverFactory creates a driver only if

RFH::IsRenderFrameLive(), and destroys the driver on

RenderFrameDeleted().



[1] https://chromiumcodereview.appspot.com/17572015



Bug: 1007974

entry.title: [mullet m2] DidAcceptSuggestion handles sub-popups.
entry.content:
The position param passed to ExternalDelegate::DidAcceptSuggestion

is not taking into account the fact that we now have sub-popups.

This has a few problems:



1. The metrics emitted are not representing what they should.

SuggestionAccepted[1] metric assumes only one level, which tells us

how well we are sorting suggestions, meaning the more often the

user chooses suggestions with position=0, the better we sorted.

However, because users can choose to fill the whole form (fillEverything) from the second level, the position is

given as 7, even tough the second level could have been open

from the first suggestion.



2. It does not allow us to measure the usage in the second/third level.



The solution is to update ExternalDelegate::DidAcceptSuggestion

inside the delegate, so that we can have the expected behaviour depending on the "sub_popup_level".



This CL is a no-op, I will start passing the sub_popup_level

information and fix the metric emission in a follow up.



[1] https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:components/autofill/core/browser/metrics/suggestions_list_metrics.cc;drc=719c18366c0226fa751f38693b00f822d1b7ea9b;l=34

entry.title: PlzDedicatedWorker: Add the field trial testing config.
entry.content:
For ease of detecting changes that do not work well with

PlzDedicatedWorker, let me add the field trial testing config

with the PlzDedicatedWorker enabled.



We followed the past attempt to update the field trial testing config:

https://chromium.googlesource.com/chromium/src/+/c8900237101eff877c5eee2c1b17928c7f1abab9

i.e.

- move expectation files in /web_tests/virtual/plz-dedicated-worker

to the non-virtual directory.

- delete dedicated-worker-service-worker-interception.html that is not

spec-compatible behavior which was added at

https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1059979

- delete dedicated-worker-reporting.html because COEP reports are sent

to worker's ReportingObserver API after PlzDedicatedWorker. Before

PlzDedicatedWorker, reports are sent to ancestor frame's

ReportingObserver but it's not spec compatible.

- delete use-counter-out-of-scope-worker.html, which was used for

measuring the impact of PlzDedicatedWorker ship for intent-to-ship.

- update "resource.type: other" to "resource.type: script".

- delete/merge "virtual/plz-dedicated-worker" expectation lines in

TestExpectations.



Removal of the "virtual/plz-dedicated-worker" directory will be

done in the future CL.

entry.title: Prerender: [3/n]: New tab triggers follow the initiator registry's limit
entry.content:
Prior to this CL, triggers with prerender-into-new-tab were not applied

to the prerender's limit. The motivation of this CL is to take them into

account under the current mechanism of prerender limit.



Under kPrerender2InNewTab, CreateAndStartHost will be called in the

newly created WebContents’s PrerenderHostRegistry for new tab triggers

rather than in initiator WebContents’s registry, while it is called in

initiator ones for normal triggers. In either case, we want to control

the limit based on the initiator WebContents. This CL adopts this

behavior.

entry.title: Make ExtensionWebRequestApiTest work with BackgroundResourceFetch
entry.content:
The asyncXhrsFromOurselfAreVisible test in

ExtensionWebRequestApiTestWithContextType.WebRequestBlocking is

currently flaky when the BackgroundResourceFetch feature is enabled.

This is because the test is checking the order of

onBeforeRequestWebRequest events for a synchronously called fetch()

request and a navigation request.



fetch(getURLHttpXHRData()).catch((e) => {

chrome.test.fail();

});

navigateAndWait(getURL("complexLoad/b.jpg"));



The order of these two requests is not guaranteed, and when the

BackgroundResourceFetch feature is enabled, the request for fetch() is

more likely to be delivered later than the navigation request.



This CL modifies the test to wait for the result of the fetch() request

before starting the navigation.



Also this CL make tests in ExtensionWebRequestApiTestWithContextType run

both with and without the BackgroundResourceFetch feature.

entry.title: Fix BackgroundURLLoader's issue in handling redirect
entry.content:
Currently there is a bug in BackgroundURLLoader that if a request

was redirected, and the request is canceld by destructing the

BackgroundURLLoader before Context::OnReceivedRedirect() is called,

FollowRedirectCallback is destructed in the main thread. The

FollowRedirectCallback was created in the backgroud thread by

ResourceRequestSender::OnReceivedRedirect(), and it must be destructed

in the background thread. When DCHECK is enable,

DCHECK_CALLED_ON_VALID_SEQUENCE() in ThreadCheckingCallbackWrapper's

destructor fails.



To fix this issue, this CL changes RequestClient::OnReceivedRedirect()

to wrap the FollowRedirectCallback with a OnTaskRunnerDeleter as

a std::unique_ptr.

So the FollowRedirectCallback must be destructed in the background

thread.

entry.title: Drop server address tables
entry.content:
Server addresses are a deprecated concept of Autofill that this chain of

CLs removes. crrev.com/c/5005347 and crrev.com/c/5004060 removed the

syncing of server addresses - and hence the writes to AutofillTable.

crrev.com/c/5005354 removed the remaining reads. See those CL

descriptions for more context on server addresses.



As such, the tables server_addresses and server_address_metadata are not

used anymore. This CL drops them, removes the CRUD operations from

AutofillTable and removes any relevant unit tests.

covert channel attacks.

[3].

[3] https://w3c.github.io/compute-pressure/#data-delivery

entry.title: Indirect virtual calls in ExceptionState
entry.content:
There are thousands of calls to the ExceptionState::Throw* methods,

sufficiently many that indirecting via the vtable in the caller adds

significantly to the binary size.



Rename the Throw* virtual methods to DoThrow* and call them indirectly

via non-inlined non-virtual methods. This will add a small performance

cost when throwing an exception, but that is assumed to be rare.



As an unrelated change, factor out common code in

NonThrowableExceptionState and DummyExceptionStateForTesting throw

methods.

entry.title: LinkPreview: Polish activation code
entry.content:
This patch rewrites the preview activation code to operate via

the PageImpl class to follow the prerendering activation design.



We can pass all relevant RenderViewHosts to perform activation

also on subframes hosted by different RenderViews. In this CL,

we are passing only the main frame's RenderViewHost yet though.



With this change, we can relax the capability controls via the

common activation code path.



Also, this change reveals an existing bug that the capability

control wasn't applied correctly if the initially created

RenderFrameHost is reused for the preview navigation.

This is because the initial RenderFrameHost is created before

WebContents::Create() returns, and WebContents::SetDelegate()

call is too late to notify the preview mode to the initial

RenderFrameHost.

To resolve this issue, this patch modifies

WebContents::CreateParams to store WebContentsDelegate and set it

immediately after the WebContents instance creation.

entry.title: VideoEncoderInfo includes support for frame size change.
entry.content:
This CL adds a new field |supports_frame_size_change| to

VideoEncoderInfo, which indicates whether the underlying encoder

supports frame size change without re-initialization. This is part of

the effort to enable dynamic frame size change for video encode

accelerator(VEA). Dynamic frame size change will not be supported by all

VEAs. If the value of this newly added field is false, client should

re-initialize VEA when frame size change is needed.



Design doc: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1QtGs7lEbXuRqAub3GxouuuvNsKpDtHzFcHkGQnnAC0c/edit?usp=sharing
